{"operation":"llm.complete_task_with_tools","payload":{"agentId":"6961092d-82fa-4591-bd84-98a2cebb163a","agentName":"Scout","baseUrl":"https://api.deepseek.com","choice":"[{\"text\":\"Based on my research, I've gathered information about product planning best practices and industry cases. Let me now create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\"},{\"id\":\"call_00_tGiWP9Z1imB9QOXnSfLV2Mi4\",\"call_id\":null,\"function\":{\"name\":\"plan_summarize\",\"arguments\":{\"input\":\"Research completed on product planning best practices and industry cases. Key findings:\\n\\n1. PRODUCT PLANNING BEST PRACTICES:\\n- Strategic Alignment: Connect product planning to business goals and market needs\\n- Customer-Centric Approach: Base planning on user research and feedback\\n- Agile Frameworks: Use Scrum, Kanban, or hybrid methodologies\\n- Roadmapping: Create visual timelines showing feature releases and milestones\\n- Prioritization: Use frameworks like RICE, MoSCoW, or Kano model\\n- Cross-functional Collaboration: Involve engineering, design, marketing, sales\\n- Data-Driven Decisions: Use analytics and metrics to guide planning\\n- Iterative Process: Regular review and adjustment cycles\\n- Risk Management: Identify and mitigate potential challenges early\\n- Stakeholder Communication: Clear updates and alignment sessions\\n\\n2. INDUSTRY CASE STUDIES & FRAMEWORKS:\\n- ProductPlan Framework: 6-step process (Discover, Define, Design, Develop, Deliver, Deploy)\\n- Agile Product Planning: Backlog grooming, sprint planning, release planning\\n- OKR-based Planning: Objectives and Key Results alignment\\n- Lean Startup Approach: Build-Measure-Learn feedback loops\\n- SAFe (Scaled Agile Framework): For enterprise product planning\\n- Design Thinking: Empathize, Define, Ideate, Prototype, Test\\n\\n3. KEY SUCCESS FACTORS:\\n- Clear product vision and strategy\\n- Market validation before development\\n- Minimum Viable Product (MVP) focus\\n- Continuous user feedback integration\\n- Flexible adaptation to market changes\\n- Balanced short-term and long-term planning\\n- Resource allocation optimization\\n- Quality assurance integration\\n\\n4. COMMON PITFALLS TO AVOID:\\n- Feature creep without prioritization\\n- Ignoring technical debt\\n- Poor stakeholder management\\n- Lack of user research\\n- Rigid planning without adaptability\\n- Siloed decision-making\\n- Inadequate success metrics\\n\\n5. TOOLS & TEMPLATES:\\n- Product roadmaps\\n- User story mapping\\n- Feature prioritization matrices\\n- Release planning calendars\\n- Stakeholder communication plans\\n- Risk assessment frameworks\\n\\nRecommendation: Implement a hybrid approach combining agile methodologies with strategic planning, using data-driven prioritization and continuous stakeholder alignment.\"}},\"signature\":null,\"additional_params\":null}]","maxTokens":2000,"maxTurns":540,"messageId":null,"model":"deepseek-chat","providerId":"deepseek","providerType":"DeepSeek","sessionId":"6f907aca-3299-45a7-a38c-c238a691a534","taskCardId":"ca94b74c-49a6-41f5-a53b-4c795d7b6290","temperature":0.8,"usage":{"cached_input_tokens":26176,"input_tokens":33064,"output_tokens":529,"total_tokens":33593},"workGroupId":"32c79005-71dc-4969-8aaa-9f59d7511499"},"phase":"completion_response","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:43:34.774005+00:00"}
